The "Why": Why would you use VARCHAR(255) instead of just TEXT for every string column?
VARCHAR: Small to medium VARCHAR data is usually stored inline (directly in the table row). This makes it very fast to fetch because the database engine finds the data exactly.
TEXT: TEXT data is often stored off-row. The table row only contains a small "pointer" to a different location on the disk where the actual text is kept. Fetching a TEXT column requires an extra "hop" to a different part of the disk,-- slows down the performance.


