The "Decimal" logic: If you are storing money, why is DECIMAL preferred over FLOAT or DOUBLE? 
FLOAT and DOUBLE are Approximate Data Types. – If you add 0.1 to 0.2 using FLOAT, the result might be 0.30000000000000004 instead of exactly 0.30. In a banking system, those tiny fractions add up to massive missing sums .
DECIMAL is a Fixed-Point Data Type.--  It stores numbers as "strings" or specialized structures where each digit is preserved exactly as it was entered.


