Questions: If a column has a FOREIGN KEY constraint, can you delete the parent row while the child row still exists? How do ON DELETE CASCADE or SET NULL change this?
By default, when we try to delete a parent row(e.g. Customer) while child row(e.g., an Order) still points to it– throws error..
	Alternate way is CASCADE and SET NULL
ON DELETE CASCADE: If you delete the parent, the database automatically deletes all associated child rows.
ON DELETE SET NULL: If you delete the parent, the child rows stay, but their Foreign Key column is changed to NULL.
